Sandton car dealership, Prestige Marques confirmed to TshisaLIVE that Cassper took delivery of a brand new Bentley Continental GT on Monday.According to Bentley South Africa the Continental GT has a starting price of R3.7 million.Prestige said that it was the second Bentley that it sourced for Cassper in a little over six months, after the rapper purchased a Bentley from the company earlier this year.The dealership later posted snaps on Instagram of Cassper collecting his new car.A photo posted by Prestige Marques (@prestige_marques) on Nov 14, 2016 at 5:20am PSTA photo posted by Prestige Marques (@prestige_marques) on Nov 14, 2016 at 5:20am PSTA photo posted by Prestige Marques (@prestige_marques) on Nov 14, 2016 at 7:15am PSTA photo posted by Prestige Marques (@prestige_marques) on Nov 14, 2016 at 6:19am PSTA photo posted by Prestige Marques (@prestige_marques) on Nov 14, 2016 at 7:15am PSTA photo posted by Prestige Marques (@prestige_marques) on Nov 14, 2016 at 6:19am PST Cassper made headlines earlier this month when a Sunday Sun report claimed that Cassper's Bentley had gone "missing". Their sources claimed that they had been told he was in an accident, but told the paper they believed he could no longer afford the cost of maintaining the vehicle and had sold it.Cassper's team refused to comment to TshisaLIVE about the allegations. Find the hottest celebrity and entertainment news on TshisaLIVE or follow TshisaLIVE on Facebook and Twitter.